docs.abstract: A consortium of which the company is a part has made working versions of ultradense seven-nanometer chips, capable of holding much more information than existing chips.
docs.snippet: A consortium of which the company is a part has made working versions of ultradense seven-nanometer chips, capable of holding much more information than existing chips.
docs.lead_paragraph: IBM said on Thursday that it had made working versions of ultradense computer chips, with roughly four times the capacity of today’s most powerful chips.

headline.main: IBM Discloses Working Version of a Much Higher-Capacity Chip
headline.print_headline: IBM Discloses Working Version of a Much Higher-Capacity Chip

docs.abstract: Facebook and other leading American technology companies see Africa as a place to experiment with new ways of expanding Internet access.
docs.snippet: Facebook and other leading American technology companies see Africa as a place to experiment with new ways of expanding Internet access.
docs.lead_paragraph: Nearly two years ago, Facebook’s chief executive, Mark Zuckerberg, announced an ambitious effort to connect the world’s poorest people to the Internet.

headline.main: Facebook and Other Tech Giants Expand Internet Access in Africa

docs.abstract: The technology company, which does most of its business overseas, said most of the decline in the second quarter was because of the strong dollar.
docs.snippet: The technology company, which does most of its business overseas, said most of the decline in the second quarter was because of the strong dollar.
docs.lead_paragraph: IBM is advancing rapidly into new fields like data analytics, cloud computing and mobile applications. And while the technology company’s second-quarter results showed encouraging progress in those businesses, it was not enough to translate into growth for the company as a whole, Steve Lohr reports.

headline.main: Daily Report: IBM Revenue Falls, Highlighting Challenges as It Shifts Course
